                    "description": "Improvement, SAP Implementation & Warehouse migration\n\n-\tDevelopment of a new PGS15 (NEN-EN 14470-1) warehouse with dangerous goods. Including three Grade D cleanrooms. During this project the complete solution and delivery of the warehouse was my responsibility (i.e. managing stakeholders, timeline, milestones, reporting and deliverables).  \n-\tImplementation of Warehouse Management System in SAP (i.e. configuration, complete flow creation, master data management, QA of SAP).\n-\tUser lead for the Implementation of the internal Warehouse and the external Warehouses, also doing all the classroom training for all the end-users in SAP. \nContent of work; Layout, SAP configuration, development of a VNA truck including the complete internal and external transportation, training employees, expert on QMS documents, purchasing all the materials and so on. We are using SMART solutions to allocate the material in the Warehouse. Creating new KPI reporting\u2019s.\n\n\nGMP/ EHS & Continuous Improvement:\n\u2022 Coordinates deviations by applying thorough Root Cause Analysis at the point of occurrence with all relevant parties involved;\n\u2022 QN coordinator in the deviation control process and is responsible for timely follow-up and defining appropriate corrective and preventive action (CAPA\u2019s);\n\u2022 Coaches employees in problem solving and RCA and drives opening of the QN within 24 hours after occurrence and closure within 30 days;\n\u2022 Ensures that the Good Housekeeping (6S) program is executed according to a standardized way of working. Develops standards and coaches all personnel at MSC; \n\u2022 Executes and drives Go to Gemba program for GMP and EHS;\n\u2022 Ensures Procedures / Processes in-line with the relevant compliance guidelines (QMS, GMP, GDP, EHS and SOX). Aligns with the right parties (compliance engineers, EHS CoE, QA etc.);\n\u2022 Supports in GMP and EHS audits;\n\u2022 Ensures that procedures describing the storage, transportation and handling of dangerous goods are compliant (e.g. PGS15)",
